definition: to inspect/to review/to read/to peruse/to go through/to experience

sentences.english: No words can express the grandeur of that parade.
sentences.chinese: 閱兵式那宏偉的場面是無法用語言來表達的。

sentences.english: A military parade down the main street of Phoenix, Ariz. , ca.
sentences.chinese: 阿下來的鳳凰城，亞利桑那州，加州主要街道閱兵式。

sentences.english: Kim Jong Il attended a military parade to mark the 65th birthday of Workers' Party of Korea (WPK).
sentences.chinese: 金正日出席閱兵式，紀念朝鮮勞動黨65歲生日。

sentences.english: Foreign military officials attending the regatta toured a Song - class diesel-electric submarine.
sentences.chinese: 參加此次閱兵式的外國軍官參觀了一艘宋級柴電潛艇。

sentences.english: 7Saudi special forces take part in a military parade, preparing for the Hajj in Mecca on November 10, 2010. (MUSTAFA OZER/AFP/Getty Images)
sentences.chinese: 沙特特種部隊參加閱兵式，爲麥加朝聖做準備。

sentences.english: Trooping the Colour is a ceremony to honour Queen Elizabeth's official birthday. The Queen celebrates her 90th birthday this year.
sentences.chinese: 皇家軍隊閱兵式的舉行是爲了給女王慶祝90歲生日。

sentences.english: To complete the military ceremony, 60 planes will fly past.
sentences.chinese: 將有60架飛機將從上空飛過，作爲閱兵式的結束。

sentences.english: There will be a big parade.
sentences.chinese: 這裏會有大型的閱兵式。
